      "side": 1,
      "message": "Interesting! I haven\u0027t run into that issue with the Persian locale before.\n\nUnfortunately the zero-padding is needed because the PDF won\u0027t validate if\nwe don\u0027t output the strings in *lexicographic* order. Sorting the strings\nseems inefficient - the idea is just to sort them numerically and output\nstrings such that the lexicographic sorting of the strings matches the\nnumeric sort too.\n\nI tried setting my locale to fa_IR but I can\u0027t reproduce the issue.\nI do see references to printf generating different digits, but only\nwhen you use the special I flag.\n\nhttps://linux.die.net/man/3/printf\n\nEven if printf did generate Arabic-Indic numerals, I believe that\nthose would still zero-pad and that sorting them lexicographically\nwould still be consistent with their numeric order - and the PDF\nspec allows UTF-8 so I think it\u0027d be fine.\n\nThe node ID isn\u0027t meant to be an ordinal or cardinal, it\u0027s just a\nnumeric ID, all that matters is that it\u0027s unique per node.\n\nI tried it with a mix of negative and positive IDs and it worked\nfine; they still sorted lexicographically.\n\nSo, I *think* this is okay still. If you still have concerns I\u0027m\nhappy to use appendS32 and manually zero-pad.",
